## (5)(a) Diversity Techniques

> Name and describe 3 diversity techniques used in cellular networks. *(5 marks)*

---

**1. Spatial Diversity**

Multiple antennas placed at different physical locations. If one antenna experiences a fade, others likely won't.

- **MIMO** uses multiple antennas at both TX and RX
- Antennas should be spaced at least λ/2 apart

---

**2. Time Diversity**

Transmit the same data at different times. Fading changes over time, so if one transmission fails, a later one may succeed.

- Implemented via **interleaving** and **ARQ retransmissions**
- Works best when channel changes faster than data rate

---

**3. Frequency Diversity**

Transmit on multiple frequencies. Different frequencies experience independent fading.

- **OFDM** spreads data across many subcarriers
- **Frequency hopping** (used in Bluetooth, GSM)

